The Dan Alhaji Foundation has called on the local and international community, as well as other Non Governmental Organisations (NGOs), to lend a helping hand to  the displaced persons in Batsari local government area of Katsina  State. According to the foundation, the insecurity ravaging Batsari LGA has made it impossible for people to go out for farming. Addressing journalists at the Unity Fountain in Abuja during a protest, the Legal Adviser of the Lawal Dan Alhaji Foundation, Emeka Nwachukwu, said the peaceful protest was to call on the federal government, as well as other Nigerians, NGOs, and the international communities, lend a hand to the people of Batsari. The foundation said the immediate need of the people is health care services and food. While calling on the government to still do more to protect the lives and property of its citizens, the foundation said the residents have deserted their homes, adding that women and children are molested by the bandits. “We urged both local and the international organisations to assist the victims of rape and insurgency in Batsari local government. The people need food, drugs and other relevant materials. Also speaking, Aminu Alqasim,  who shared his recent experience in Batsari LGA, said many people have run away from their farms.      